Australia Closes in on Victory in Opening Test Against Sri Lanka

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-09-02T13:43:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/australia-closes-in-on-victory-in-opening-test-against-sri-lanka.html
Australia reduced  Sri Lanka  to 120-5
at the end of the third day of their opening cricket Test to
close in on victory Test.  Mahela Jayawardene is 57 not out as Sri Lanka chases a
victory total of 379. He teamed with Angelo Mathews, who scored
32, for a 53-run stand to end the day in Galle after Prasanna
Jayawardene was dismissed by  Ryan Harris  without scoring.  Harris took 3-24, while Shane Watson and Mitchell Johnson
claimed one wicket each.  Michael Clarke scored 60 as Australia was bowled out for
210 in their second innings. Sri Lanka was bowled out for 105 in
its first innings in reply to the visitors’ 273.  Fifth-ranked  Australia  would move above Sri Lanka into
fourth in the International Cricket Council’s Test Championship
standings by winning the best-of-three contest. It’s Australia’s
first elite Test since January and Clarke’s first Test as
captain since replacing Ponting.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 